===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# An [[organized]] culture encompassing many [[community|communities]], often on the scale of a [[nation]] or a [[people]]; a stage or system of social, political{{,}} or technical development.
#: {{ux|en|the Aztec '''civilization'''}}
#: {{ux|en|Western '''civilization'''}}
#: {{ux|en|Modern '''civilization''' is a product of industrialization and globalization.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Human society, particularly [[civil]] society.
#: {{ux|en|A hermit doesn't much care for '''civilization'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|I'm glad to be back in '''civilization''' after a day with that rowdy family.}}
# The act or process of [[civilize|civilizing]] or becoming [[civilize|civilized]].
#: {{ux|en|The teacher's '''civilization''' of the child was no easy task.}}
# The state or quality of being [[civilized]].
#: {{ux|en|He was a man of great '''civilization'''.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} The act of rendering a criminal process civil.

